From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: qsliu <qsliu2017@outlook.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 10:55:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] bundle-setup: include all static archives under extension/*/

The bundle-library target's glob `lib*_extension.a` only copies the
thin C++ wrapper archive each extension ships. Extensions that produce
additional companion archives (notably vortex, whose Rust
implementation lives in `libvortex_duckdb.a` and whose
`libvortex_extension.a` is only a ~4KB wrapper with `_vortex_init_rust`
as an UNDEFINED reference) were silently excluded from the bundle,
causing `undefined symbol` failures at load time for static-bundle
consumers.

Widen the glob to `lib*.a` so all archives produced under
extension/<name>/ land in the bundle.
---
 Makefile | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Makefile b/Makefile
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -540,7 +540,7 @@ bundle-setup:
 	mkdir -p bundle && \
 	cp src/libduckdb_static.a bundle/. && \
 	cp third_party/*/libduckdb_*.a bundle/. && \
-	cp extension/*/lib*_extension.a bundle/. && \
+	cp extension/*/lib*.a bundle/. && \
 	find vcpkg_installed -name '*.a' -exec cp {} bundle/. \; && \
 	cd bundle && \
 	find . -name '*.a' -exec mkdir -p {}.objects \; -exec mv {} {}.objects \; && \
--
